 S_1 = 7, 
 S_2 = 7 + 7/2 = 7(1+1/2), 
 S_3 = 7 + 7/2 + 7/4 = 7(1+1/2+1/4), 
 S_n = 7 (1+1/2+\cdots+1/2^{n-1}). 
 S = 7 (1+1/2+1/4+\cdots) = 7 \cdot 2 = 14. 
 S - S_n < 0.01. 
 S_n = 7 (1+1/2+\cdots+1/2^{n-1}) = 7 \frac{{1 - (1/2)^n }}{{1 - 1/2}} = 14(1 - 1/2^n ), 
 14 - 14(1 - 1/2^n ) < 0.01, 
 14/2^n < 0.01, 
